## Pipeline Overview

The full pipeline runs in the following order:

```
1. extract-datasets.py            — extract glycosites (predicted + experimental) and variants
2. map-datasets.py                — map variants relative to glycosites
3. run-binomial-test.py		  — run two-sided binomial test on relative positions 
4. make-plotdata-binomial.py      — compute fold change and produce plots with binomial two-sided statistical significance stars

```

Step-1: extracting glycosite and variant datasets
-------------------------------------------------
This script extracts two types of datasets — glycosylation sites and missense variants — for use in downstream mapping and plotting analysis. It is run from the command line with options for species, dataset type, and release version.

The glycosite extraction function produces two files which contain the experimentally verified glycosites and the predicted glycosites in GlyGen.  

The variant extraction function creates one dataset which is separated into "germline" data which are nonsynonymous single-nucleotide variants (SNVs) from our germline variant dataset, and "somatic_cancer" data which are SNVs associated with cancer from the BioMuta Database.

## Input files:
The following dataset are expected in the directory:
reviewed/human_protein_mutation_cancer_all.csv
reviewed/human_protein_mutation_germline_all.csv
reviewed/human_proteoform_glycosylation_sites_*.csv

## Usage - run the following:
$ python3 extract-datasets.py -d glycosites   #outputs --> /data/human_glycosites_experimental.csv and /data/human_glycosites_predicted.csv

$ python3 extract-datasets.py -d variants   #outputs --> /data/human_variants_missense.csv


Step-2: mapping glycosite and variant datasets 
-----------------------------------------------
Mapping script which finds all variant-site pairs where the variant falls within ±20 amino acids of a glycosylation site, then maps the relative position of that variant to the glycosylation site.

## Input files:
The following dataset are expected in the directory: 
/data/human_glycosites_experimental.csv 
/data/human_glycosites_predicted.csv
/data/human_variants_missense.csv

## Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -g GLYCOTYPE, --glycotype=GLYCOTYPE
                        N-linked/O-linked
  -v VARTYPE, --vartype=VARTYPE
                        somatic_cancer/germline
  -t SITETYPE, --sitetype=SITETYPE
                        predicted/experimental

## Usage:
$ python3 map-datasets.py -g N-linked -v somatic_cancer -t predicted    #outputs --> /data/mapping.human.n_linked.somatic_cancer_predicted.csv

$ python3 map-datasets.py -g O-linked -v germline -t experimental    #outputs --> /data/mapping.human.o_linked.germline_experimental.csv


Step-3: binomial test 
---------------------
For each relative position in the mapping datasets, the script runs a two-sided binomial test to determine if the number of variants observed at each position are significantly different from what you'd expect by chance.

## Input files:
Precomputed mapping test results are expected in the directory with the naming convention:
data/mapping.human.{glycotype}.{vartype}_{sitetype}.csv
e.g. mapping.human.o_linked.germline_experimental.csv

## Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i INFILE, --infile=INFILE
                        single mapping file to process
  -a, --all             run binomial test on all mapping files in data/

## Usage:
To run the test on an individual dataset use:
python3 run-binomial-test.py -i data/mapping.human.n_linked.germline_all_experimental.csv   #output --> /data/binomial_test.mapping.human.n_linked.germline_experimental.csv

To run on all mapping datasets in the data folder use:
python3 run-binomial-test.py -a


Step-4: computes fold change and plots
------------------------------------------------
This script computes fold change statistics and produces plots from the mapping files. Each run produces a separate plot with positions +/−6 amino acids relative to either N-linked or O-linked predicted or experimental glycosylation sites, for both germline and somatic_cancer lines.

## Significance Annotation
The output is a p-value per position, which the plotting script then uses to add significance stars (*, **, ***) to the plot. Positions without a star show no significant deviation from the expected mutation rate.

| Symbol | p-value threshold |
|---|---|
| `*` | p < 0.05 |
| `**` | p < 0.01 |
| `***` | p < 0.001 |

## Input files:
Precomputed binomial mapping results are expected in the directory with the naming convention:
data/binomial_test.mapping.human.{glycotype}.{vartype}_{sitetype}.csv
e.g. binomial_test.mapping.human.n_linked.somatic_cancer_all_experimental.csv

## Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -g GLYCOTYPE, --glycotype=GLYCOTYPE
                        N-linked/O-linked
  -v VARTYPE, --vartype=VARTYPE
                        all/somatic/germline
  -t SITETYPE, --sitetype=SITETYPE
                        predicted/experimental

## Usage:
python3 make-plotdata.py -g N-linked -v all -t experimental    #outputs --> /plots/plot.human.n_linked.all_experimental.png & /plots/plotdata.human.n_linked.all_experimental.json
